notesStmt.note: 376 leaves foliated (Part 1) [i], 1-263; (Part 2) 1-5, 5-6, 6-63; (Part 3) 1-46, [i], upper left and lower right verso; the first part comprises the first seven sections of the text, the second part is the eighth section, and the third part is the ninth section of the work.
Mistakes covered over in yellow or blacked out; some corrections and additions in margins; significant syllables, words, or phrases highlighted in red throughout. Several folios colored yellow.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Grammatical treatise and commentary that develops and expands on Patañjali's early work, the Mahābhāṣya ('Great commentary'), a treatment of Pāṇini's sūtras. Mansucript comprises nine sections, although foliation occurs in three parts.

msItem.title: Śabdakaustubha
शब्दकौस्तुभ
msItem.colophon: Colophon: iti śrīvidvanmukuṭaratnasyaṃ lakṣmo 'dharasūreḥ sūnunā bhaṭṭojidīkṣitena kṛte ṣabdakaustubhe prathamādhyāyasya prathame pāde navamamānhikaṃ pādaścāpaṃ samāptaḥ // (f. 46v).
